obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE ADVOCATES ACT, 1961`
  line __________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line _________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `B AR C OUNCILS`
  line `3. State Bar Councils.`
  line `4. Bar Council of India.`
  line `5. Bar Council to be bod y corporate.`
  line `6. Functions of State Bar Councils.`
  line `7. Functions of Bar Council of India.`
  line `7A. Membership in international bodies.`
  line `8. Term of office of members of State Bar Council.`
  line `8A. Constitution of special Committee in the absence of election.`
  line `9. Discipli nary committees.`
  line `9A. Constitution of legal aid committees.`
  line `10. Constitution of committees other than disciplinary committees.`
  line `10A. Transaction of business by Bar Councils and committees thereof.`
  line `10B. Disqualification of members of Bar Council.`
  line `11. Staff of Bar Council.`
  line `12. Accounts and audit.`
  line `13. Vacancies in Bar Council and committees thereof not to invalidate action taken.`
  line `14. Election to Bar Council s not to be questioned on certain grounds.`
  line `15. Power to make rules.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `A DMISSION AND ENROLME NT OF ADVOCATES`
  line `16. Senior and other advocates.`
  line `17. State Bar Councils to maintain roll of advocates.`
  line `18. Transfer of name from one State roll to another.`
  line `19. State Bar Councils to send copies of rolls of advocates to the Bar Council of India.`
  line `20. Special provision for enrolment of certain Supreme Court advocates.`
  line `21. Disputes regarding seniority.`
  line `22. Certificate of enrolment.`
  line `23. Right of pre - audience.`
