obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `24. Persons who may be admitted as advocates on a State roll.`
  line `24A. Disqualification for enrolme nt.`
  line `25. Authority to whom applications for enrolment may be made.`
  line `26. Disposal of applications for admission as an advocate.`
  line `26A. Power to remove names from roll.`
  line `27. Application once refused not to be entertained by another Bar Council except in certain c ircumstances.`
  line `28. Power to make rules.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `R IGHT TO PRACTISE`
  line `29. Advocates to be the only recognised class of persons entitled to practise law.`
  line `30. Right of advocates to practise.`
  line `31. [ Repealed.].`
  line `32. Power of court to permit appearances in particul ar cases.`
  line `33. Advocates alone entitled to practise.`
  line `34. Power of High Courts to make rules.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `C ONDUCT OF ADVOCATES`
  line `35. Punishment of advocates for misconduct.`
  line `36. Disciplinary powers of Bar Council of India.`
  line `36A. Changes in constitution of discipli nary committees.`
  line `36B. Disposal of disciplinary proceedings.`
  line `37. Appeal to the Bar Council of India.`
  line `38. Appeal to the Supreme Court.`
  line `39. Application of sections 5 and 12 of Limitation Act, 1963.`
  line `40. Stay of order.`
  line `41. Alteration in roll of advocates.`
  line `42. P owers of disciplinary committee.`
  line `42A. Powers of Bar Council of India and other committees.`
  line `43. Cost of proceedings before a disciplinary committees.`
  line `44. Review of orders by disciplinary committee.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `45. Penalty for persons illegally practising in courts and before other authorities.`
  line `45A. Power to frame and publish lists of touts.`
  line `46. [ Repealed.].`
  line `46A. Financial assistance to State Bar Council.`
  line `47. Reciprocity.`
  line `48. Indemnity against legal proceedings.`
  line `48A. Power of revision.`
  line `48AA. Re view.`
