  line 3
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `48B. Power to give directions.`
  line `49. General power of the Bar Council of India to make rules.`
  line `49A. Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  line `50. Repeal of certain enactments.`
  line `51. Rule of construction.`
  line `52. Saving.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `T EMPORARY AND TR ANSITIONAL PROVISIONS`
  line `53. Elections to first State Bar Council.`
  line `54. Term of office of members of first State Bar Councils.`
  line `55. Rights of certain existing legal practitioners not affected.`
  line `56. Dissolution of existing Bar Councils.`
  line `57. Power to make rules pe nding the constitution of a Bar Council.`
  line `58. Special provisions during the transitional period.`
  line `58A. Special provisions with respect to certain advocates.`
  line `58AA. Special provisions in relation to the Union territory of Pondicherry.`
  line `58AB. Special provisions with respect to certain persons enrolled by Mysore State Bar Council.`
  line `58AC. Special provisions with respect to certain persons enrolled by Uttar Pradesh State Bar Council.`
  line `58AD. Special provisions with respect to certain persons migrating to India.`
  line `58AE. S pecial provisions in relation to the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu.`
  line `58AF. Special provisions in relation to Jammu and Kashmir.`
  line `58AG. Special provisions in relation to articled clerks.`
  line `58B. Special provision relating to certain disciplinary proceedi ngs.`
  line `59. Removal of difficulties.`
  line `60. Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  line `T HE SCHEDULE.`
