  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( a ) “ advocate ” means an advocate entered in any roll under the provisions of this Act;`
  line `( b ) “ appointed day ”, in relation to any provision of this Act, means the day on which that provision comes into`
  line force;
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( d ) “ Bar Council ” means a Bar Council constituted under this Act;`
  line `( e ) “ Bar Council of India ” means the Bar Council constituted under section 4 for the territories to which this Act`
  line extends;
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( g ) “ High Court ”, except in sub - section ( 1 ) 3 [and sub - section ( 1A )] of section 34 and in sections 42 and 43, doe s`
  line `not include a court of the Judicial Commissioner, and, in relation to a State Bar Council, means, --`
  line `( i ) in the case of a Bar Council constituted for a State or for a State and one or more Union territories, the`
  line `High Court for the State;`
  line `( ii ) in the cas e of the Bar C ouncil constituted for Delhi, 4 [the High Court of Delhi];`
  line `( h ) “ law graduate ” means a person who has obtained a bachelor's degree in law from any University established`
  line `by law in India;`
  line `( i ) “ legal pr actitioner ” means an advocate 5 [or vakil] of any High Court, a pleader, mukhtar or revenue agent;`
  line `( j ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( k ) “ roll ” means a roll of advocates prepared and maintained under this Act;`
  line `( l ) “ State ” does not include a Union territory;`
  line `( m ) “ St ate Bar Council ” means a Bar Council constituted under section 3;`
  line `( n ) “ State roll ” means a roll of advocates prepared and maintained by a State Bar Council under section 17.`
  line `3 [( 2 ) Any reference in this Act to a law which is not in force 6 *** in the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu,`
  line `shall, in relation to 7 *** that territory, be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that State`
  line `or that territory, as the case may be.]`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `B AR C OUNCILS`
  line `3. State Bar Councils. ― ( 1 ) Th ere shall be a Bar Council —`
  line `( a ) for each of the States of Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, Gujarat, 8 [Jammu and Kashmir,] 9 [Jharkhand], 10 [ Madhya`
  line `Pradesh and Chhattisgarh], 11 ***, 12 ***, 13 [Karnataka], Orissa, 14 [ Rajasthan, Telangana 15 [ Uttar Pradesh ],`
  line `16 [ Uttaranchal, Megh alya, Manipur and Tripura ] ], to be known as the Bar Council of that State;`
  line `1. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 107 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15 - 10 - 1976).`
  line `2. Clause ( f ) omitted by Act 60 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “ the High Court of Punjab ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Subs. b y Act 107 of 1976, s. 2, for “ vakil or attorney ” (w.e.f. 15 - 10 - 1976).`
  line `6. The words “in the State of Jammu and Kashmir or” omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central`
  line `Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18 - 3 - 2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation`
  line `(Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23 - 10 - 2020).]`
  line `7. The words “that State or” omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (A daptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide`
  line `notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18 - 3 - 2020) Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws)`
  line `Order, 2020, notification No. S.O.3774(E), dated (23 - 10 - 2020).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 60 of 197 3, s. 4 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 30 of 2000, s. 28 (w.e.f. 15 - 11 - 2000).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 28 of 2000, s.24, for “and Madhya Pradesh” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 2000).`
  line `11. The word “ Madras ” omitted by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and Sch. 4.`
  line `1 2. The word “ Maharashtra ” omitted by Reg. 8 of 1963, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1965).`
  line `1 3. Subs. by the Mysore State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1974, for “ Mysore ”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1973).`
  line `1 4. Subs. by Act 6 of 2014, s. 34, for “ Rajas than, Uttar Pradesh ” (w.e.f. 2 - 6 - 2014).`
  line `1 5. Subs. by Act 29 of 2000, s. 29, for “and Uttar Pradesh” (w.e.f. 9 - 11 - 2000).`
  line `1 6. Subs. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 9, for “ and Uttaranchal” (w.e.f. 23 - 3 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
