  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `1 [( b ) for the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Mizoram and Nagaland to be known as the Bar`
  line `Council of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Mizoram and Nagaland;]`
  line `( c ) for the State of Ker ala and the Union territory of 2 [ La kshadweep] to be known as the Bar Council`
  line `of Kerala;`
  line `3 [( cc ) for the 4 [State of Tamil Nadu] and the Union territory of Pondicherry to be known as the Bar`
  line `Council of Madras;]`
  line `5 [( ccc ) for the States of Maharashtra and Goa and the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and`
  line `Daman and Diu, to be known as the Bar Council of Maharashtra and Goa;]`
  line `6 [( d ) for the States of Punjab and Haryana and the Union territory of Chandigarh, to be known as the`
  line `Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana;`
  line `( dd ) for the State of Himachal Pradesh, to be known as the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh;]`
  line `( e ) for the State of West Bengal and the 7 [Union territory of Andaman and Nicobar Islands], to be`
  line `known as the Bar Council of West Bengal; and`
  line `( f ) for the Union territory of Delhi, to be known as the Bar Council of Delhi.`
  line `( 2 ) A State Bar Council shall consist of the following members, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) in the case of the State Bar Council of Delhi, the Additional Solicitor - General of India, ex officio;`
  line `8 [ 9 [ in the case of the State Bar Council s of Assam, Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram and Nagaland, the`
  line `Advocate - General of each of the States of Assam, A runachal Pradesh, Mizoram and Nagaland] ex officio;`
  line `in the case of the State Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana, the Advocate - General of each of the States of`
  line `Punjab and Haryana, ex officio;] and in the case of any other State Bar Council, the Advocate - Gen eral of`
  line `the State, ex officio;`
  line `10 [( b ) in the case of a State Bar Council with an electorate not exceeding five thousand, fifteen`
  line `members, in the case of a State Bar Council with an electorate exceeding five thousand but not exceeding`
  line `ten thousand, twenty m embers, and in the case of a State Bar Council with an electorate exceeding ten`
  line `thousand, twenty - five members, elected in accordance with the system of proportional representation by`
  line `means of the single transferable vote from amongst advocates on the elect oral roll of the State Bar`
  line `Council:]`
  line `11 [Provided that as nearly as possible one - half of such elected members shall, subject to any rules that`
  line `may be made in this behalf by the Bar Council of India, be persons who have for at least ten years been`
  line `advocates o n a State roll, and in computing the said period of ten years in relation to any such person,`
  line `there shall be included any period during which the person has been an advocate enrolled under the Indian`
  line `Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926).]`
  line `1. S ubs. by Acts 26 of 2012, s. 9, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 23 - 3 - 2013 ).`
  line `2. Subs. by the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (Alteration of Name) Act, 1973 (34 of 19 73), s. 5, for “the Laccadive,`
  line `Minicoy and Amindivi Islands” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1973).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and the Sch.`
  line `4. Subs. by the Madras State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1970, for “ State of Madras ”`
  line `(w.e.f. 14 - 1 - 1969).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 18 of 1987, s. 21, for cl ause ( ccc ) (w.e.f. 30 - 5 - 1987).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 53 of 1970, s. 24, for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 25 - 1 - 1971).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 81 of 1971, s. 34, for “ Union territories of Tripura and the Andaman and Nicobar Islands ” (w.e.f. 21 - 1 - 1972).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 9, for “in the case of the State Bar C ouncil of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura, the`
  line `Advocate - General of each of the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Nagaland and Tripura” (w.e.f. 23 - 3 - 2013).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 4, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `1 1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
