obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `1 [( 3 ) There shall be a Chairman and a Vice - Chairman of each State Bar Council elected by the Council in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3A ) Every person holding office as Chairman or as Vice - Chairman of any State Bar Council immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Ad vocates (Amendment) Act, 1977 (38 of 1977), shall, on such`
  line `commencement, cease to hold office as Chairman or Vice - Chairman, as the case may be:`
  line `Provided that every such person shall continue to carry on the duties of his office until the Chairman or`
  line `the V ice - Chairman, as the case may be, of each State Bar Council, elected after the commencement of the`
  line `Advocates (Amendment) Act, 1977 (38 of 1977), assumes charges of the office.]`
  line `1 [( 4 ) An advocate shall be disqualified from voting at an election under sub - s ection ( 2 ) or for being`
  line `chosen as, and for being, a member of a State Bar Council, unless he possesses such qualifications or satisfies`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed in this behalf by the Bar Council of India, and subject to any such rules`
  line `that may be made, an electoral roll shall be prepared and revised from time to time by each State Bar Council.`
  line `( 5 ) Nothing in the proviso to sub - section ( 2 ) shall affect the term of office of any member elected before`
  line `the commencement of the Advocates (Amendment) Act, 1964 (21 of 1964), but every election after such`
  line `commencement shall be held in accordance with the provisions of the rules made by the Bar Council of India`
  line `to give effect to the said proviso.]`
  line `2 [( 6 ) Nothing in clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 2 ) shall affe ct the representation of elected members in any`
  line `State Bar Council as constituted immediately before the commencement of the Advocates (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1973 (60 of 1973), until that State Bar Council is reconstituted in accordance with the provisions of thi s Act.]`
  line `4. Bar Council of India. ― ( 1 ) There shall be a Bar Council for the territories to which this Act extends to`
  line `be known as the Bar Council of India which shall consist of the following members, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) the Attorney - General of India, ex officio;`
  line `( b ) the Solicitor - General of India, ex officio;`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) one member elected by each State Bar Council from amongst its members.`
  line `4 [( 1A ) No person shall be eligible for being elected as a member of the Bar Council of India unless he`
  line `posse sses the qualifications specified in the proviso to sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3.]`
  line `5 [( 2 ) There shall be a Chairman and a Vice - Chairman of the Bar Council of India elected by the Council`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2A ) A person holding office as Chairman or as Vice - Chairman of the Bar Council of India immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Advocates (Amendment) Act, 1977 (38 of 1977), shall, on such`
  line `commencement, cease to hold office as Chairman or Vice - Chairman, as the case may be:`
  line `Provided that such person shall continue to carry on the duties of his office until the Chairman or the`
  line `Vice - Chairman, as the case may be, of the Council, elected after the commencement of the Advocates`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1977 (38 of 1977), assumes charge of the offi ce.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1977, s. 2, for sub - section s ( 3 ) and ( 3A ) (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1977).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Clause ( bb ) omitted by Act 38 of 1977, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1977).`
  line `4. I ns. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 5 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 38 of 1977, s. 3, for sub - section s ( 2 ) and ( 2A ) (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1977).`
