obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `1 [( 3 ) The term of office of a member of the Bar Council of India elected by the State Bar Council shall, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of a member of a State Bar Council who holds office ex officio, be two years from the`
  line `date of his election 2 [or till he ceases t o be a member of the State Bar Council, whichever is earlier]; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, be for the period for which he holds office as a member of the State Bar`
  line `Council:`
  line `Provided that every such member shall continue to hold office as a member of the Bar Council of India`
  line `until his successor is elected.]`
  line `5. Bar Council to be body corporate. ― Every Bar Council shall be a body corporate having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal, with power to acquire and hold property, both movable and immovable, and t o`
  line `contract, and may be the name by which it is known sue and be sued.`
  line `6. Functions of State Bar Councils. ― ( 1 ) The functions of a State Bar Council shall be ―`
  line `( a ) to admit persons as advocates on its roll;`
  line `( b ) to prepare and maintain such roll;`
  line `( c ) to en tertain and determine cases of misconduct against advocates on its roll;`
  line `( d ) to safeguard the rights, privileges and interests of advocates on its roll;`
  line `3 [( dd ) to promote the growth of Bar Associations for the purposes of effective implementation of the`
  line `welfare schemes referred to in clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of this section and clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 7;]`
  line `( e ) to promote and support law reform;`
  line `4 [( ee ) to conduct seminars and organise talks on legal topics by eminent jurists and publ ish journals`
  line `and papers of legal interest;`
  line `( eee ) to organise legal aid to the poor in the prescribed manner;]`
  line `( f ) to manage and invest the funds of the Bar Council;`
  line `( g ) to provide for the election of its members;`
  line `3 [( gg ) to visit and inspect Universitie s in accordance with the directions given under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 7;]`
  line `( h ) to perform all other functions conferred on it by or under this Act;`
  line `( i ) to do all other things necessary for discharging the aforesaid functions.`
  line `5 [( 2 ) A State Bar Council may constitute one or more funds in the prescribed manner for the purpose of —`
  line `( a ) giving financial assistance to organise welfare schemes for the indigent, disabled or other`
  line advocates;
  line `( b ) giving legal aid or advice in accordance with th e rules made in this behalf;`
  line `3 [( c ) establishing law libraries.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 5 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 2 (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
