obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `( 3 ) A State Bar Council may receive any grants, donations, gifts or benefactions for all or any of the`
  line `purposes specified in sub - section ( 2 ) which shall be credited to the appropriate fund or funds constituted under`
  line `that sub - section.]`
  line `7. Functions of Bar Council of India. ― 1 [( 1 )] The functions of the Bar Council of India shall be ―`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) to lay down standards of professional conduct and etiquette for advocates;`
  line `( c ) to lay down the procedure to be followed by its disciplinary committee and the disciplinary`
  line `committee of each State Bar Council;`
  line `( d ) to safeguard the rights, privileges and interests of advocates;`
  line `( e ) to promote and support law reform;`
  line `( f ) to deal with and dispose of any matter arising under this Act, which may be referred to it by a State`
  line `Bar Council;`
  line `( g ) to exercise general supervision and control over State Bar Councils;`
  line `( h ) to promote legal education and to lay down standards of such education in cons ultation with the`
  line `Universities in India imparting such education and the State Bar Councils;`
  line `( i ) to recognise Universities whose degree in law shall be a qualification for enrolment as an advocate`
  line `and for that purpose to v isit and inspect Universities 3 [o r cause the State Bar Councils to visit and inspect`
  line `Universities in accordance with such directions as it may give in this behalf];`
  line `4 [( ia ) to conduct seminars and organise talks on legal topics by eminent jurists and publish journals`
  line `and papers of legal i nterest;`
  line `( ib ) to organise legal aid to the poor in the prescribed manner;`
  line `( ic ) to recognise on a reciprocal basis foreign qualifications in law obtained outside India for the`
  line `purpose of admission as an advocate under this Act;]`
  line `( j ) to manage and invest the funds of the Bar Council;`
  line `( k ) to provide for the election of its members;`
  line `( l ) to perform all other functions conferred on it by or under this Act;`
  line `( m ) to do all other things necessary for discharging the aforesaid functions.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) The Bar Council o f India may constitute one or more funds in the prescribed manner for the purpose`
  line `of —`
  line `( a ) giving financial assistance to organise welfare schemes for indigent, disabled or other advocates;`
  line `( b ) giving legal aid or advice in accordance with the rules made i n this behalf.`
  line `5 [( c ) establishing law libraries.]`
  line `( 3 ) The Bar Council of India may receive any grants, donations, gifts or benefactions for all or any of the`
  line `purposes specified in sub - section ( 2 ) which shall be credited to the appropriate fund or funds c onstituted under`
  line `that sub - section.]`
  line `1. Section 7 r e - numbered as sub - section ( 1 ) of that section by Act 60 of 1973, s. 7 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Clause ( a ) omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Added by Act 70 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 7 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
