  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `1 [ 7A. Membership in international bodies. ― The Bar Council of India may become a member of`
  line `international legal bodies such as the International Bar Association or the International Legal Aid Association,`
  line `contribute such s ums as it thinks fit to such bodies by way of subscription or otherwise and authorise`
  line `expenditure on the participation of its representatives in any international legal conference or seminar.]`
  line `2 [ 8. Term of office of members of State Bar Council. ― The term o f office of an elected member of a`
  line `State Bar Council (other than an elected member thereof referred to in section 54) shall be five years from the`
  line `date of publication of the result of his election:`
  line `Provided that where a State Bar Council fails to provide for the election of its members before the expiry`
  line `of the said term, the Bar Council of India may, by order, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the said`
  line `term for a period not exceeding six months.`
  line `8A. Constitution of Special Committee in the abse nce of election. ― ( 1 ) Where a State Bar Council fails`
  line `to provide for the election of its members before the expiry of the term of five years or the extended term, as`
  line `the case may be, referred to in section 8, the Bar Council of India shall, on and from the date immediately`
  line `following the day of such expiry, constitute a Special Committee consisting of ―`
  line `( i ) the ex officio member of the State Bar Council referred to in clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 3 to be the Chairman:`
  line `Provided that where there ar e more than one ex officio members, the senior most amongst them shall`
  line `be the Chairman; and`
  line `( ii ) two members to be nominated by the Bar Council of India from amongst advocates on the`
  line `electoral roll of the State Bar Council,`
  line `to discharge the functions of the State Bar Council until the Bar Council is constituted under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) On the constitution of the Special Committee and until the State Bar Council is constituted —`
  line `( a ) all properties and assets vesting in the State Bar Council shall vest in the Sp ecial Committee;`
  line `( b ) all rights, liabilities and obligations of the State Bar Council, whether arising out of any contract or`
  line `otherwise, shall be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Special Committee;`
  line `( c ) all proceedings pending before the Sta te Bar Council in respect of any disciplinary matter or`
  line `otherwise shall stand transferred to the Special Committee.`
  line `( 3 ) The Special Committee constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) shall, in accordance with such directions as`
  line `the Bar Council of India may give to it in this behalf, hold elections to the State Bar Council within a period of`
  line `six months from the date of its constitution under sub - section ( 1 ), and where, for any reason the Special`
  line `Committee is not in a position to conduct election within the said pe riod of six months, the Bar Council of`
  line `India may, for reasons to be recorded by it in writing, extend the said period.]`
  line `3 [ 9. Disciplinary committees. ― ( 1 ) A Bar Council shall constitute one or more disciplinary committees,`
  line `each of which shall consist of three persons of whom two shall be persons elected by the Council from`
  line `amongst its members and the other shall be a person co - opted by the Council from amongst advocates who`
  line `possess the qualifications specified in the proviso to sub - section ( 2 ) of section 3 and who are not members of`
  line `the Council, and the senior - most advocate amongst the members of a disciplinary committee shall be the`
  line `Chairman thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), any disciplinary committee constituted prior to`
  line `the commencement of the Advocates (A mendment) Act, 1964 (21 of 1964 ) may dispose of the proceedings`
  line `pending before it as if this section had not been amended by the said Act.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 8 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 4, for section 8 (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 5, for section 9 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
