  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `1 [ 9A. Constitution of legal aid committees. ― ( 1 ) A Bar Council may constitute one or more legal aid`
  line `committees each of which shall consist of such number of members, not exceeding nine but not less than five,`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) The qualifications, the method of selection and the term of office of the members of a legal aid`
  line `committee shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
  line `10. Constitution of committees other than disciplinary committees. ― ( 1 ) A State Bar Council shall`
  line `constitute the following standing committees, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) an executive committee consisting of five members elected by the Council from amongst its`
  line members;
  line `( b ) an enrolment committee consisting of three members elected by the Council from amongst its`
  line members.
  line `( 2 ) The Bar Council of India shall constitute the following standing committees, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) an executive committee consisting of nine members elected by the Council from amongst its`
  line members;
  line `( b ) a legal education committee consisting of ten members, of w hom five shall be persons elected by`
  line `the Council from amongst its members and five shall be persons co - opted by the Council who are not`
  line `members thereof.`
  line `( 3 ) A State Bar Council and the Bar Council of India may constitute from amongst its members such oth er`
  line `committees as it may deem necessary for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `2 [ 10A. Transaction of business by Bar Councils and committees thereof. ― 3 [( 1 ) The Bar Council of`
  line `India shall meet at New Delhi or at such other place as it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line determine.
  line `( 2 ) A State Bar Council shall meet at its headquarters or at such other place as it may, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, determine.]`
  line `( 3 ) The committees other than disciplinary committees constituted by the Bar Councils shall meet at the`
  line `headquarters of the respective Bar Councils.`
  line `( 4 ) Every Bar Council and every committee thereof except the disciplinary commit tees shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at their meetings as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 5 ) The disciplinary committees constituted under section 9 shall meet at such times and places and shall`
  line `observe such rules of pro cedure in regard to the transaction of business at their meetings as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line `4 [ 5 [ 10B.] Disqualification of members of Bar Council. ― An elected member of a Bar Council shall be`
  line `deemed to have vacated his office if he is declared by the Bar Counci l of which he is a member to have been`
  line `absent without sufficient excuse from three consecutive meetings of such Council, or if his name is, for any`
  line `cause, removed from the roll of advocates or if he is otherwise disqualified under any rule made by the Bar`
  line `Council of India.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 9 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 5, for sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `5. Section 10 A r e - numbered as section 10B of the Ac t by Act 60 of 1973, s. 10 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `11. Staff of Bar Council. ― ( 1 ) Every Bar Council shall appoint a secretary and may appoint an`
  line `accountant and such number of other persons on its staff as it may deem necessary.`
  line `( 2 ) The secretary and the accountant, if any, shall possess such qualifications as may be prescribed.`
  line `1 2. Accounts and Audit. ― ( 1 ) Every Bar Council shall cause to be maintained such books of accounts`
  line `and other books in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of a Bar Council shall be audited by auditors duly qualified to act as auditors of`
  line `companies under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), at such times and in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `1 [( 3 ) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each financial year, but not later than the 31st day of`
  line `December of the year next fol lowing, a State Bar Council shall send a copy of its accounts together with a`
  line `copy of the report of the auditors thereon to the Bar Council of India and shall cause the same to be published`
  line `in the official Gazette.`
  line `( 4 ) As soon as may be practicable at the end of each financial year, but not later than the 31 st day of`
  line `December of the year next following, the Bar Council of India shall send a copy of its accounts together with`
  line `a copy of the report of the auditors thereon to the Central Government and shall c ause the same to be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India.]`
  line `13. Vacancies in Bar Council and committees thereof not to invalidate action taken. ― No act done by`
  line `a Bar Council or any committee thereof shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of`
  line `any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Council or committee, as the case may be.`
  line `14. Election to Bar Councils not to be questioned on certain grounds. ― No election of a member to a`
  line `Bar Council shall be called in question on the ground merely that due notice thereof has not been given to any`
  line `person entitled to vote thereat, if notice of the date has, not less than thi rty days before that date, been`
  line `published in the Official Gazette.`
  line `15. Power to make rules. ― ( 1 ) A Bar Council may make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for ―`
  line `2 [( a ) the election of members of the Bar Council by secret ballot including the conditions subject to`
  line `which persons can exercise the right to vote by postal ballot, the preparation and revision of electoral rolls`
  line `and the manner in which the results of election shall be published;]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( c ) the manner of electio n of the Chairman and the Vice - Chairman of the Bar Council;]`
  line `( d ) the manner in which and the authority by which doubts and disputes as to the validity o f a n`
  line `election to the Bar Council 4 [or to the office of the Chairman or Vice - Chairman] shall be finally decided;`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `( f ) the filling of casual vacancies in the Bar Council;`
  line `( g ) the powers and dutie s of the Chairman and the Vice - Chairma n of the Bar Council;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 11, for sub - section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, for clause ( a ), ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Clause ( b ) omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 38 of 1977, s. 5 (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1977).`
  line `5. Clause ( e ) omitted by Act 2 3 of 196 6, s. 3 (w.e.f. 3 - 9 - 1966 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
