  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `1 [( ga ) the constitution of one or more funds by a Bar Council for the purpose of giving financial`
  line `assistance or giving legal ai d or advice referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 6 and sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 7;`
  line `( gb ) organisati on of legal aid and advice to the poor, constitution and f unctions of committees and`
  line `sub - committees for that purpose and description of proceedings in connection with which legal aid or`
  line `advice may be given;]`
  line `( h ) the summoning and holding o f meetings of th e Bar Council, 2 *** the conduct of business thereat,`
  line `and the number of members necessary to constitute a quorum;`
  line `( i ) the constitution and functions of any committee of the Bar Council and the term of office of`
  line `members of any such committee;`
  line `( j ) the summo ning and holding of meetings, the conduct of business of any such committee, and the`
  line `number of members necessary to constitute a quorum;`
  line `( k ) the qualifications and the conditions of service of the secretary, the accountant and other`
  line `employees of the Bar C ouncil;`
  line `( l ) the maintenance of books of accounts and other books by the Bar Council;`
  line `( m ) the appointment of auditors and the audit of the accounts of the Bar Council;`
  line `( n ) the management and investment of the funds of the Bar Council.`
  line `( 3 ) No rules made under this section by a State Bar Council shall have effect unless they have been`
  line `approved by the Bar Council of India.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `ADMISSION AND ENROLMENT OF ADVOCATES`
  line `16. Senior and other advocates. ― ( 1 ) There shall be two classes of advocates, namely, senior advocates`
  line `and other advocates.`
  line `( 2 ) An advocate may, with his consent, be designated as senior advocate if the Supreme Court or a High`
  line `Court is of opinion t hat by virtue of his ability, 3 [standin g at the Bar or special knowledge or experience in`
  line `law] he is deserving of such distinction.`
  line `( 3 ) Senior advocates shall, in the matter of their practice, be subject to such restrictions as the Bar Council`
  line `of India may, in the interests of the legal profes sion, prescribe.`
  line `( 4 ) An advocate of the Supreme Court who was a senior advocate of that Court immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall, for the purposes of this section, be deemed to be a senior advocate:`
  line `4 [Provided that where any such senior advocate makes an application before the 31st December, 1965 to`
  line `the Bar Council maintaining the roll in which his name has been entered that he does not desire to continue as`
  line `a senior advocate, the Bar Council may grant the application and the roll shall be altered accordingly.]`
  line `17. State Bar Councils to maintain roll of advocates. ― ( 1 ) Every State Bar Council shall prepare and`
  line `maintain a roll of advocates in which shall be entered the names and addresses of —`
  line `( a ) all persons who were entered as advocates on the roll of any High Court under the Indian Bar`
  line `Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 192 6), immedia tely before the appointed day 5 [including persons, being citizens`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 12 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. The words “the times and places where such meetings are to be held” omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “ experience and standing at the Bar ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 8 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 14, for “ and who, within the prescribed time ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
