obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `of India, who before the 15th day of August, 1947, were enrolled as advocates under the said Act in any`
  line `area which before the said date was comprised within India as defined in th e Government of India`
  line `Act, 1935 and who at any time] express an intention in the prescribed manner to practise within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the Bar Council;`
  line `( b ) all other persons who are admitted to be advocates on the roll of the State Bar Council under t his`
  line `Act on or after the appointed day.`
  line `( 2 ) Each such roll of advocates shall consist of two parts, the first part containing the names of senior`
  line `advocates and the second part, the names of other advocates.`
  line `( 3 ) Entries in each part of the roll of advocate s prepared and maintained by a State Bar Council under this`
  line `section shall be in the order of seniority, 1 [and, subject to any rule that may be made by the Bar Council of`
  line `India in this behalf, such seniority shall be determined] as follows: ―`
  line `( a ) the seniority of an advocate referred to in clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with his date of enrolment under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926);`
  line `( b ) the seniority of any person who was a senior advocate o f the Supreme Court immediately before`
  line `the appointed day shall, for the purposes of the first part of the State roll, be determined in accordance`
  line `with such principles as the Bar Council of India may specify;`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( d ) the seniority of an y other person who, on or after the appointed day, is enrolled as a senior`
  line `advocate or is admitted as an advocate shall be determined by the date of such enrolment or admission, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line `3 [( e ) notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( a ), t he seniority of an attorney enrolled [whether`
  line `before or after the commencement of the Advocates (Amendment) Act, 1980 (47 of 1980)] as an advocate`
  line `shall be determined in accordance with the date of his enrolment as an attorney.]`
  line `( 4 ) No person shall be enr olled as an advocate on the roll of more than one State Bar Council.`
  line `18. Transfer of name from one State roll to another. ― ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 17, any person whose name is entered as an advocate on the roll of any State Bar Council may make`
  line `an application in the prescribed form to the Bar Council of India for the transfer of his name from the rol l of`
  line `that State Bar Council to the roll of any other State Bar Council and, on receipt of any such application the`
  line `Bar Council of India shall direct that the name of such person shall, without the payment of any fee, be`
  line `removed from the roll of the first m entioned State Bar Council and entered in the roll of the other State Bar`
  line `Council and the State Bar Councils concerned shall comply with such direction:`
  line `4 [Provided that where any such application for transfer is made by a person against whom any disciplin ary`
  line `proceeding is pending or where for any other reason it appears to the Bar Council of India that the application`
  line `for transfer has not been made bona fide and that the transfer should not be made, the Bar Council of India`
  line `may, after giving the person mak ing the application an opportunity of making a representation in this behalf,`
  line `reject the application.]`
  line `( 2 ) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that where on an application made by an advocate`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ), his name is transferred from the roll of one State Bar Council to that of another, he shall`
  line `retain the same seniority in the latter roll to which he was entitled in the former roll.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 9, for “and such seniority shall be determined” (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `2. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 60 of 1973, s. 14 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 47 of 1980, s. 2 (29 - 11 - 1980).`
  line `4. The proviso added by Act 21 of 1964, s. 10 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
