  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `19. State Bar Councils to send copies of rolls of advocates to the Bar Council of India. ― Every State`
  line `Bar Council shall send to the Bar Council of India an authenticated copy of the roll of advocates prepared by`
  line `it for the first time under this Act and shall thereafter communicate to the Bar Council of India all alterations`
  line `in and additions to any such rol l, as soon as the same have been made.`
  line `1 [ 20. Special provision for enrolment of certain Supreme Court advocates. ― ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Chapter, every advocate who was entitled as of right to practise in the Supreme`
  line `Court immediately before the appointed day and whose name is not entered in any State roll may, within the`
  line `prescribed time, expr ess his intention in the prescribed form to the Bar Council of India for the entry of his`
  line `name in the roll of a State Bar Council and on receipt thereof the Bar Council of India shall direct that the`
  line `name of such advocate shall, without payment of any fee, be entered in the roll of that State Bar Council, and`
  line `the State Bar Council concerned shall comply with such direction.`
  line `( 2 ) Any entry in the State roll made in compliance with the direction of the Bar Council of India under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) shall be made in the order of seniority determined in accordance with the provisions of sub -`
  line `section ( 3 ) of section 17.`
  line `( 3 ) Where an advocate referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) omits or fails to express his intention within the`
  line `prescribed time, his name shall be entered in the roll of the State Bar Council of Delhi.]`
  line `21. Disputes regarding seniority. ― ( 1 ) Where the date of seniority of two or more persons is the same,`
  line `the one senior in age shall be reckoned as senior to the other.`
  line `2 [( 2 ) Subject as aforesaid, if any dispute arises with respect to the seniority of any person, it shall be`
  line `referred to the State Bar Council concerned for decision.]`
  line `3 [ 22. Certificate of enrolment. ― ( 1 ) There shall be issued a certificate of enrolment in the prescribed`
  line `form by the State Bar Council to every person whose name is entered in the roll of advocates maintained by it`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person whose name is so entered in the State roll shall notify any change in the place of his`
  line `permanent residence to the State Bar Council concerned within ninety days of such change.]`
  line `23. Right of pre - audience. ― ( 1 ) The Attorney - General of India shall have pre - audience over all other`
  line advocates.
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), the Solicitor - General of India shall have pre - audience over`
  line `all other advocates.`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to the provisions of sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Additional Solicitor - General of India shall`
  line `have pre - audience over all other advocates.`
  line `4 [( 3A ) Subject to the provisions of sub - sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ), the second Additional Solicitor - G eneral`
  line `of India shall have pre - audience over all other advo cates.]`
  line `( 4 ) Subject to the pr ovisions of sub - sections ( 1 ), 5 [( 2 ), ( 3 ) and ( 3A )], the Advocate - General of any State`
  line `shall have pre - audience over all other advocates, and the right of pre - audience among Advocates - General`
  line `inter se shall be determined by thei r respective seniority.`
  line `( 5 ) Subject as aforesaid —`
  line `( i ) senior advocates shall have pre - audience over other advocates, and`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 15, for section 20 (w.e.f. 3 1 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 22 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 47 of 1980, s. 3 (w.e.f. 29 - 11 - 1980).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “ ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) ” (w.e.f. 29 - 11 - 1980).`
