obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `( ii ) the right of pre - audience of senior advocates inter se and other advocates inter se shall be`
  line `determined by their respective seni ority.`
  line `24. Persons who may be admitted as advocates on a State roll. ― ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, and the rules made thereunder, a person shall be qualified to be admitted as an advocate on a State roll, if`
  line `he fulfils the following conditions, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) he is a citizen of India:`
  line `Provided that subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, a national of any other country may be`
  line `admitted as an advocate on a State roll, if citizens of India, duly qualified, are permitted to practise l aw in that`
  line `other country;`
  line `( b ) he has completed the age of twenty - one years;`
  line `( c ) he has obtained a degree in law —`
  line `( i ) before the 1 [12th day of March, 1967], from any University in the territory of India; or`
  line `( ii ) before the 15th day of August, 1947, from any University in any area which was comprised`
  line `before that date within India as defined by the Government of India Act, 1935; or`
  line `2 [( iii ) after the 12th day of March, 1967, save as provided in sub - clause ( iiia ), after undergoing a`
  line `three - year course of stud y in law from any University in India which is recognised for the purposes of`
  line `this Act by the Bar Council of India; or`
  line `( iiia ) after undergoing a course of study in law, the duration of which is not less than two`
  line `academic years commencing from the academic year 1967 - 68 or any earlier academic year from any`
  line `University in India which is recognised for the purposes of this Act by the Bar Council of India; or]`
  line `3 [( iv ) in any other case, from any University outside the territory of India, if the degree is`
  line `recogn ised for the purposes of this Act by the Bar Council of India; or]`
  line `4 [he is a barrister and is called to the Bar on or before th e 31st day of December, 1976; 5 [or has passed`
  line `the article clerk's examination or any other examination specified by the High Cou rt at Bombay or`
  line `Calcutta for enrolment as an attorney of that High Court;] or has obtained such other foreign`
  line `qualification in law as is recognised by the Bar Council of India for the purpose of admission as an`
  line `advocate under this Act];`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `( e ) he fulfils such other conditions as may be specified in the rules made by the State Bar Council`
  line `under this Chapter;`
  line `7 [( f ) he has paid, in respect of the enrolment, stamp duty, if any, chargeable under the Indian Stamp`
  line `Act, 1899 (2 of 1899), and an enrolment fee payabl e to the State Bar Council of 8 [ six hundred rupees and`
  line `to the Bar Council of India, one hundred and fifty rupees by way of a bank draft drawn in favour of that`
  line `Council:]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 18, for “ 28th day of February, 1963 ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub - clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 196 4, s. 13 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 18, for “ he is a barrister ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 107 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15 - 10 - 1976).`
  line `6. Clause ( d ) omitted by Act 60 of 1973, s. 18 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for clause ( f ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 6, for “two hundred and fifty rupees” (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
