obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `Provided that where such person is a member of the Scheduled C astes or the Scheduled Tribes and`
  line `produces a certificate to that effect from such authority as may be prescribed, the enrolment fee payable`
  line `by him to t he State Bar Council shall be 1 [one hundred rupees and to the Bar Council of India, twenty - five`
  line rupees.]
  line `2 [ Explanation. ― For the purposes of this sub - section, a person shall be deemed to have obtained a`
  line `degree in law from a University in India on the date on which the results of the examination for that`
  line `degree are published by the University on its notice board or otherwise declaring him to have passed that`
  line examination.]
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), 3 [a vakil or a pleader who is a law graduate]`
  line `may be admitted as an advocate on a State roll if he —`
  line `( a ) makes an application for such enrolment in accordance with the provisions of this Act, not later`
  line `than two years from the appointed day; and`
  line `( b ) fulfils the conditions specified in clauses ( a ), ( b ), ( e ) and ( f ) of sub - section ( 1 ).`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ) a perso n who —`
  line `( a ) 5 *** has, for at least three years, been a vakil or a pleader or a mukhtar, or was entitled at any tim e`
  line `to be enrolled under any law 6 *** as an advocate of a High Court (including a High Court of a former Part`
  line `B State) or of a Court of Judicial Commissioner in any Union territory; or`
  line `7 [( aa ) before the 1st day of December, 1961, was entitled otherwise than as an advocate to practise the`
  line `profession of law (whether by way of pleading or acting or both) by virtue of the provisions of any law, or`
  line `who would have been so entitled had he not been in public service on the said date; or]`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) before the 1st day of April, 1937, has been an advocate of any High Court in any area which was`
  line `comprised within Burma as defined in the Gover nment of India Act, 1935 (25 & 26 Geo. 5 C 42); or`
  line `( d ) is entitled to be enrolled as an advocate under any rule made by the Bar Council of India in this`
  line behalf,
  line `may be admitted as an advocate on a State roll if he —`
  line `( i ) makes an application for such enrol ment in accordance with the provisions of this Act; and`
  line `( ii ) fulfils the conditions specified in clauses ( a ), ( b ), ( e ) and ( f ) of sub - section ( 1 ). ]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 [ 24A. Disqualification for enrolment. ― ( 1 ) No person shall be admitted as an advoca te on a State`
  line `roll ―`
  line `( a ) if he is convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude;`
  line `( b ) if he is convicted of an off ence under the provisions of the Untouchability (O ffences) Act, 1955`
  line `(22 of 1955);`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 6, for “one hundred and twenty - five rupees” (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 14 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30 - 3 - 1962).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 13, for certain words ( w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `5. The words, figures and letter “ before the 31st day of March, 1964, ” omitted by Act 33 of 1968, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5 - 6 - 1968).`
  line `6. The words “ then in force ” omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 5 - 6 - 1968).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 18 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `8. Clause ( b ) omitted by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `9. S ub - section ( 4 ) o mitted by Act 107 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15 - 10 - 1976).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 19 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
