  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `1 [( c ) if he is dismissed or removed from employment or office under the State on any charge`
  line `involving moral turpitude.`
  line `Explanation. ― In this clause, the expression “ State ” shall have the meaning assigned to it under`
  line `article 12 of the Constitution:]`
  line `Provided that the disqualification for enrolment as aforesai d shall cease to have effect after a period of`
  line `tw o years has elapsed since his 2 [released or dismissal or, as the case may be, removal. ]`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub - section ( 1 ) shall apply to a person who having been found guilty is dealt`
  line `with under the provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958).]`
  line `25. Authority to whom applications for enrolment may be made. ― An application for admission as an`
  line `advocate shall be made in the prescribed form to the State Bar Council within whose jurisdiction the applicant`
  line `proposes to practise.`
  line `26. Disposal of applications for admission as an advocate. ― ( 1 ) A State Bar Council shal l refer every`
  line `application for admission as an advocate to its enrolment committee, and subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub - sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) 3 [and to any direction that may be given in writing by the State Bar Council in this`
  line `behalf], such committee shall dispose of the application in the prescribed manner:`
  line `4 [Provided that the Bar Council of India may, if satisfied, either on a reference made to it in this behalf or`
  line `otherwise, that any person has got his name entered on the roll of advocates by misreprese ntation as to an`
  line `essential fact or by fraud or undue influence, remove the name of such person from the roll of advocates after`
  line `giving him an opportunity of being heard.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the enrolment committee of a State Bar Council proposes to refuse any such application, it shall`
  line `refer the application for opinion to the Bar Council of India and every such reference shall be accompanied by`
  line `a statement of the grounds in support of the refusal of the application.`
  line `( 3 ) The enrolment committee of a State Bar Counc il shall dispose of any application referred to the Bar`
  line `Council of India under sub - section ( 2 ) in conformity with the opinion of the Bar Council of India.`
  line `3 [( 4 ) Where the enrolment committee of a State Bar Council has refused any application for admission as`
  line `an advocate on its roll, the State Bar Council shall, as soon as may be, send intimation to all other State Bar`
  line `Councils about such refusal stating the name, address and qualifications of the person whose application was`
  line `refused and the grounds for the refusal.]`
  line `5 [ 26A. Power to remove names from roll. ― A State Bar Council may remove from the State roll the`
  line `name of any advocate who is dead or from whom a request has been received to that effect.]`
  line `27. Application once refused not to be entertained by anoth er Bar Council except in certain`
  line `circumstances. ― Where a State Bar Council has refused the application of any person for admission as an`
  line `advocate on its roll, no other State Bar Council shall entertain an application for admission of such person as`
  line `an advoc ate on its roll, except with the previous consent in writing of the State Bar Council which refused the`
  line `application and of the Bar Council of India.`
  line `28. Power to make rules. ― ( 1 ) A State Bar Council may make rules to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Chapter.
  line `1. Ins. by Act 70 of 199 3, s. 7 (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for “release” (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 14 (w.e.f.16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `4. The proviso added by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `5. Subs. b y Act 60 of 1973, s. 20, for section 26A (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-19
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Page 19`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for —`
  line `1 [( a ) the time within which and form in which an advocate shall express his intention for the entry of`
  line `his name in the roll of a State Bar Counci l under section 20;]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) the form in which an application shall be made to the Bar Council for admission as an advocate`
  line `on its roll and the manner in which such application shall be disposed of by the enrolment committee of`
  line `the Bar Council;`
  line `( d ) the conditions subject to which a person may be admitted as an advocate on any such roll;`
  line `( e ) the instalments in which the enrolment fee may be paid.`
  line `( 3 ) No rules made under this Chapter shall have effect unless they have been approved by the Bar Council`
  line `of India.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `R IGHT TO PRACTISE`
  line `29. Advocates to be the only recognised class of persons entitled to practise law. ― Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and any rules made thereunder, there shall, as from the appointed day, be only one class`
  line `of persons entitled to practise the profession of law, namely, advocates.`
  line `30. Right of advocates to practise. ― Subject to the pro visions of this Act, every advocate whose name is`
  line `entered in the 3 [State roll] shall be entitled as of right to practise throughout the territories to which this Act`
  line `extends, ―`
  line `( i ) in all courts including the Supreme Court;`
  line `( ii ) before any tribunal or per son legally authorised to take evidence; and`
  line `( iii ) before any other authority or person before whom such advocate is by or under any law for the`
  line `time being in force entitled to practise.`
  line `31. [ Special provision for attorneys.]. ― Omitted by t he Advocates (Am endment) Act, 1976 ( 107 of 1 976 ),`
  line `s. 7 ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1977).`
  line `32. Power of court to permit appearances in particular cases. ― Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Chapter, any court, authority, or person may permit any person, not enrolled as an advocate under this`
  line `Act, to appear before it or him in any particular case.`
  line `33. Advocates alone entitled to practise. ― Except as otherwise provided in this Act or in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, no person shall, on or after the appointed day, be entit led to practise in any court or`
  line `before any authority or person unless he is enrolled as an advocate under this Act.`
  line `34. Power of High Courts to make rules. ― ( 1 ) The High Court may make rules laying down the`
  line `conditions subject to which an advocate shall be permitted to practise in the High Court and the courts`
  line `subordinate thereto.`
  line `4 [( 1A ) The High Court shall make rules for fixing and regulating by taxation or otherwise the fees payable`
  line `as costs by any party in respect of the fees of his adversary's advocate upon all proceedings in the High Court`
  line `or in any Court subordinate thereto.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 21, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Clause ( b ) omitted by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for “common roll” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `1 [( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provis ions contained in sub - section ( 1 ), the High Court at Calcutta may`
  line `make rules providing for the holding of the Intermediate and the Final exa minations for articled clerks to be`
  line `passed by the persons referred to in section 58AG for the purpose of being admitted as advocates on the State`
  line `roll and any other matter connected therewith.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `C ONDUCT OF ADVOCATES`
  line `35. Punishme nt of advocates for misconduct. ― ( 1 ) Where on receipt of a complaint or otherwise a State`
  line `Bar Council has reason to believe that any advocate on its roll has been guilty of professional or other`
  line `misconduct, it shall refer the case for disposal to its disciplinary committee.`
  line `3 [( 1A ) Th e S tate Bar Council may, either of its own motion or on application made to it by any person`
  line `interested, withdraw a proceeding pending before its disciplinary committee and direct the inquiry to be made`
  line `by any other disciplinary committee of that State Bar Co uncil.]`
  line `( 2 ) The disciplinary co mmittee of a State Bar Council 4 *** shall fix a date for the hearing of the case and`
  line `shall cause a notice thereof to be given to the advocate concerned and to the Advocate - General of the State.`
  line `( 3 ) The disciplinary committe e of a State Bar Council after giving the advocate concerned and the`
  line `Advocate - General an opportunity of being heard, may make any of the following orders, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) dismiss the complaint or, where the proceedings were initiated at the instance of the S tate Bar`
  line `Council, direct that the proceedings be filed;`
  line `( b ) reprimand the advocate;`
  line `( c ) suspend the advocate from practice for such period as it may deem fit;`
  line `( d ) remove the name of the advocate from the State roll of advocates.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an advocate is suspended from practice under clause ( c ) of sub - section ( 3 ), he shall, during the`
  line `period of suspension, be debarred from practising in any court or before any authority or person in India.`
  line `( 5 ) Where any notice is issued to the Advocate - General under sub - section ( 2 ), the Advocate - General may`
  line `appear before the disciplinary committee of the State Bar Council either in person or through any advocate`
  line `appearing on his behalf.`
  line `5 [ Explanation. ―In this section, 3 [section 37 and section 38], the expressions “ Advoca te - General ” and`
  line `“ Advocate - General of the State ” shall, in relation to the Union territory of Delhi, mean the Additional`
  line `Solicitor General of India.]`
  line `36. Disciplinary powers of Bar Council of India. ― ( 1 ) Where on receipt of a complaint or otherwise the`
  line `Bar C ouncil of India has reaso n to believe that any advocate 6 *** whose name is not entered on any State roll`
  line `has been guilty of professional or other misconduct, it shall refer the case for disposal to its disciplinary`
  line committee.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, the disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of`
  line `India may, 7 [either of its own motion or on a report by any State Bar Council or on an application made to it`
  line `1. In s. by Act 38 of 1977, s. 6 (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1977).`
  line `2. Sub - section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 107 of 1976, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1977).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 24 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. The words “, if it does not summarily reject the complaint, ” omitted by s. 24, ib id. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 17 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `6. The words “ on the common roll ” omitted by Act 60 of 1973, s. 25 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for “ of its own motion ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
