  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `by any person interested], withdraw for inquiry before itself any proc eedings for disciplinary action against`
  line `any advocate pending before the disciplinary committee of any State Bar Council and dispose of the same.`
  line `( 3 ) The disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India, in disposing of any case under this section,`
  line `shall observe, so far as may be, the procedure laid down in section 35, the references to the Advocate - General`
  line `in that section being construed as references to the Attorney - General of India.`
  line `( 4 ) In disposing of any proceedings under this section the disciplina ry committee of the Bar Council of`
  line `India may make any order which the disciplinary committee of a State Bar Cou ncil can make under`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ) of section 35, and where any proceedings ha ve been withdrawn for inquiry 1 [before the`
  line `di sciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India], the State Bar Council concerned shall give effect to any`
  line `such order.`
  line `2 [ 36A. Changes in constitution of disciplinary committees. ― Whenever in respect of any proceedings`
  line `under section 35 or section 36, a disciplinary committee of the State Bar Council or a disciplinary committee`
  line `of the Bar Council of India ceases to exercise jurisdiction and is succeeded by another committee which ha s`
  line `and exercises jurisdiction, the disciplinary committee of the State Bar Council or the disciplinary committee`
  line `of the Bar Council of India, as the case may be, so succeeding may continue the proceedings from the stage at`
  line `which the proceedings were so left by its predecessor committee.`
  line `36B. Disposal of disciplinary proceedings. ― ( 1 ) The disciplinary committee of a State Bar Council shall`
  line `dispose of the complaint received by it under section 35 expeditiously and in each case the proceedings shall`
  line `be concluded within a period of one year from the date of the receipt of the complain t or the date of initiation`
  line `of the proceedings at the instance of the State Bar Council, as the case may be, failing which such proceedings`
  line `shall stand transferred to the Bar Council of India which may dispose of the same as if it were a proceeding`
  line `withdra wn for inquiry under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 36.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where on the commencement of the Advocates`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1973 (60 of 1973), any proceedings in respect of any disciplinary matter against an`
  line `advocate is pending before the disciplinary committee of a State Bar Council, that disciplinary committee of`
  line `the State Bar Council shall dispose of the same within a period of six months from the date of such`
  line `commencement or within a period of one year fro m the date of the receipt of the complaint or, as the case may`
  line `be, the date of initiation of the proceedings at the instance of the State Bar Council, whichever is later, failing`
  line `which such proceedings shall stand transferred to the Bar Council o f India fo r disposal under sub - section ( 1 ).]`
  line `37. Appeal to the Bar Council of India. ― ( 1 ) Any person aggrieved by an order of the disciplinary`
  line `committe e of a State Bar Council made 3 [under section 35] 4 [or the Advocate - General of the State] may,`
  line `within sixty days of the date of the communication of the order to him, prefer an appeal to the Bar Council of`
  line India.
  line `( 2 ) Every such appeal shall be heard by the disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of In dia which may`
  line `pass such order 4 [ ( including an order varying the pun ishment awarded by the disciplinary committee of the`
  line `State Bar Council)] thereon as it deems fit:`
  line `4 [Provided that no order of the disciplinary committee of the State Bar Council shall be varied by the`
  line `disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India so as to prejudicially affect the person aggrieved without`
  line `giving him reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 0 of 1973, s. 25, for “ before the Bar Council of India ” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 18, for “ under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 35 ” (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 27 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
