obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `38. Appeal to the Supreme Court. ― Any person aggrieved by an order made by the disciplinary`
  line `committee of the Bar Council of India u nder section 36 or section 37 1 [or the Attorney - General of India or the`
  line `Advocate - General of the State concerned, as the case may be,] may, within sixty days of the date on which the`
  line `order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to the Supreme Court and the Supr eme Court may pass such`
  line `order 1 [ ( including an order varying the punishment awarded by the disciplinary committee of the Bar Council`
  line `of India)] thereon as it deems fit:`
  line `1 [Provided that no order of the disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India shall be varied b y the`
  line `Supreme Court so as to prejudicially affect the person aggrieved without giving him a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard.]`
  line `2 [ 39. Application of sections 5 and 12 of Limitation Act, 1963. ― The provisions of sections 5 and 12 of`
  line `the Limitation Act, 1 963 (36 of 1963), shall, so far as may be, apply to appeals under section 37 and section`
  line 38.]
  line `40. Stay of order. ― 3 [( 1 )] An appeal, made under section 37 or section 38, shall not operate as a stay of`
  line `the order appealed against, but the disciplinary committe e of the Bar Council of India, or the Supreme Court,`
  line `as the case may be, may, for sufficient cause, direct the stay of such order on such terms and conditions as it`
  line `may deem fit.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) Where an application is made for stay of the order before the expirati on of the time allowed for`
  line `appealing therefrom under section 37 or section 38, the disciplinary committee of the State Bar Council, or the`
  line `disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India, as the case may be, may, for sufficient cause, direct the`
  line `stay of such order on such terms and conditions as it may deem fit.]`
  line `41. Alteration in roll of advocates. ― ( 1 ) Where an order is made under this Chapter reprimanding or`
  line `suspending an advocate, a record of the punishment shall be entered against his name —`
  line `( a ) in th e case of an advocate whose name is entered in a State roll, in that roll;`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `and where any order is made removing an advocate from practice, his name shal l be struck off the State roll`
  line `6 ***.`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) Where any advocate is suspended or removed from practice, the certificate granted to him under`
  line `section 22, in respect of his enrolment shall be recalled.`
  line `42. Powers of disciplinary committee. ― ( 1 ) The disciplinary committee of a Bar Council shall have the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of`
  line `the following matters, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line `( b ) requiring discovery and production of any documents;`
  line `( c ) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line `( d ) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line `( e ) issuing commissions for the examinatio n of witnesses or documents;`
  line `( f ) any other matter which may be prescribed:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 28 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for section 39 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Section 40 re - numbered as sub - section ( 1 ) of that section by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Clause ( b ) omitted by s. 31, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `6. The words “or the common roll, as the case may be” omitted by s. 31, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `7. Sub - section ( 2 ) omitted by s. 31, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
