obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `Provided that no such disciplinary committee shall have the right to require the attendance of —`
  line `( a ) any presiding officer of a court except with the previous sanction of the High Court to which such`
  line `court is subordinate;`
  line `( b ) any officer of a revenue court except with the previous sanction of the State Government.`
  line `( 2 ) All proceedings before a disciplinary committee of a Bar Council shall be deemed to be judicial`
  line `proceedings within the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and every`
  line `such disciplinary committee shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 480, 482 and 485`
  line `of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 1 (5 of 1898).`
  line `( 3 ) F or the purposes of exercising any of the powers conferred by sub - section ( 1 ), a disciplinary`
  line `committee may send to any civil court in the territories to which this Act extends, any summons or other`
  line `process, for the attendance of a witness or the production of a document required by the committee or any`
  line `commission which it desires to issue, and the civil court shall cause such process to be served or such`
  line `commission to be issued, as the case may be, and may enforce any such process as if it were a process fo r`
  line `attendance or production before itself.`
  line `2 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding the absence of the Chairman or any member of a disciplinary committee on a date`
  line `fixed for the hearing of a case before it, the disciplinary committee may, if it so thinks fit, hold or continu e the`
  line `proceedings on the date so fixed and no such proceedings and no order made by the disciplinary committee in`
  line `any such proceedings shall be invalid merely by reason of the absence of the Chairman or member thereof on`
  line `any such date:`
  line `Provided that no fi nal orders of the nature referred to in sub - section ( 3 ) of section 35 shall be made in any`
  line `proceeding unless the Chairman and other members of the disciplinary committee are present.`
  line `( 5 ) Where no final orders of the nature referred to in sub - section ( 3 ) of section 35 can be made in any`
  line `proceedings in accordance with the opinion of the Chairman and the members of a disciplinary committee`
  line `either for want of majority opinion amongst themselves or otherwise, the case, with their opinion thereon,`
  line `shall be lai d before the Chairman of the Bar Council concerned or if the Chairman of the Bar Council is acting`
  line `as the Chairman or a member of the disciplinary committee, before the Vice - Chairman of the Bar Council,`
  line `and the said Chairman or the Vice - Chairman of the Bar Council, as the case may be, after such hearing as he`
  line `thinks fit, shall deliver his opinion and the final order of the disciplinary committee shall follow such opinion.]`
  line `3 [ 42A. Powers of Bar Council of India and other committees. ― The provisions of section 42 shall, so`
  line `far as may be, apply in relation to the Bar Council of India, the enrolment committee, the election committee,`
  line `the legal aid committee, or any other committee of a Bar Council as they apply in relation to the discip linary`
  line `commit ee of a Bar Council.]`
  line `43. Cost of proceedings before a disciplinary committees. ― The disciplinary committee of a Bar`
  line `Council may make such order as to the costs of any proceedings before it as it may deem fit and any such`
  line `order shall be execut able as if it were an order ―`
  line `( a ) in the case of an order of the disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India, of the Supreme`
  line Court;
  line `( b ) in the case of an order of the disciplinary committee of a State Bar Council, of the High Court.`
  line `44. Review of o rders by disciplinary committee. ― The disciplinary committee of a Bar Council may of`
  line `its own motion or otherwise review any order 4 [within sixty days of the date of that order, ] passed by it under`
  line `this Chapter:`
  line `1. See now the Code of C riminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974), ss. 345( 1 ), 346 and 349.`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 32 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `Provided that no such order of review of the disciplinary committee of a State Bar Council shall have`
  line `effect unless it has been approved by the Bar Council of India.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `45. Penalty for persons illegally practising in courts and before other authorities. ― Any person who`
  line `practises in any court or before any authority or person, in or before whom he is not entitled to practise under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months.`
  line `1 [ 45A. Power to frame and publish lists of touts. — ( 1 ) Every High Court, District Judge, Sessions`
  line `Judge, District Magistrate, and every Revenue - officer, not being below the rank of a Collector of a district`
  line `(each as regards their or his own Court and the Courts, if any, subordinate thereto) may fra me and publish lists`
  line `of persons proved to their or his satisfaction, or to the satisfaction of any subordinate Court as provided in`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ) by evidence of general repute or otherwise, habitually to act as touts, and may, from time to`
  line `time, alter an d amend such lists.`
  line `Explanation. — The passing of a resolution, declaring any person to be or not to be a tout, by a majority of`
  line `the members present at a meeting, specially convened for the purpose, of an association of persons entitled to`
  line `practice as legal practitioners in any Court or revenue - office, shall be evidence of the general repute of such`
  line `person for the purposes of this sub - section.`
  line `( 2 ) No person's name shall be included in any such list until he shall have had an opportunity of showing`
  line `cause aga inst such inclusion.`
  line `( 3 ) Any authority empowered under sub - section ( 1 ) to frame and publish a list of touts may send to any`
  line `Court subordinate to such authority the names of any persons alleged or suspected to be touts, and order that`
  line `Court to hold an inqui ry in regard to such persons; and the subordinate Court shall thereupon hold an inquiry`
  line `into the conduct of such persons and, after giving each such person an opportunity of showing cause as`
  line `provided in sub - section ( 2 ), shall report to the authority which has ordered the inquiry the name of each such`
  line `person who has been proved to the satisfaction of the subordinate Court to be a tout; and that authority may`
  line `include the name of any such person in the list of touts framed and published by that authority:`
  line `Prov ided that such authority shall hear any such person who, before his name has been so included,`
  line `appears before it and desires to be heard.`
  line `( 4 ) A copy of every such list shall be kept hung up in every Court to which the same relates.`
  line `( 5 ) The Court or Judge m ay, by general or special order, exclude from the precincts of the Court any`
  line `person whose name is included in any such list.`
  line `( 6 ) Any person who acts as a tout whilst his name is included in any such list shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may exte nd to three months, or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
  line `( 7 ) For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ Judge ” means the presiding judicial officer in every Civil and Criminal Court, by whatever title`
  line `he is designated;`
  line `( b ) “ su bordinate Court ” means all Courts subordinate to the High Court, including Courts of Small`
  line `Causes established under any law for the time being in force;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30 - 09 - 2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-25
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Page 25`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `( c ) “ revenue - office ” includes all Courts (other than Civil Courts) trying suits under any law for the`
  line `t ime being in force relating to landholders and their tenants or agents;`
  line `( d ) “ tout ” means a person —`
  line `( i ) who procures, in consideration of any remuneration moving from any legal practitioner, the`
  line `employment of the legal practitioner in any legal business; or who proposes to any legal practitioner`
  line `or to any person interested in any legal business to procure, in consideration of any remuneration`
  line `moving from either of them, the employment of the legal practitioner in such business; o r`
  line `( ii ) who for the purposes of such procurement frequents the precincts of Civil or Criminal Courts`
  line `or of revenue - offices, or railway stations, landing stages, lodging places or other places of public`
  line `resort. ]`
  line `[ 46. Payment of part of enrolment fees to the Bar Council of India ]. ― Omit ted by Act 70 of 1993, s. 8`
  line `( w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 19 93 ).`
  line `1 [ 46A. Financial assistance to State Bar Council. ― The Bar Council of India may, if it is satisfied that`
  line `any State Bar Council is in need of funds for the purpose of performing its functions under this Act, g ive such`
  line `financial assistance as it deems fit to that Bar Council by way of grant or otherwise.]`
  line `47. Reciprocity. ― ( 1 ) Where any country, specified by the Central Government in this behalf by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, prevents citizens of India from practising the profession of law or subjects`
  line `them to unfair discrimination in that country, no subject of any such country shall be entitled to practise the`
  line `profession of law in India.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), the Bar Counci l of India may prescribe the conditions, if`
  line `any, subject to which foreign qualifications in law obtained by persons other than citizens of India shall be`
  line `recognised for the purpose of admission as an advocate under this Act.`
  line `48. Indemnity against legal pro ceedings. ― No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any Bar`
  line `Council or any committee thereof or a member of a Bar Council 2 [or any committee thereof] for any act in`
  line `good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or of any rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line `3 [ 48A. Power of revision. ― ( 1 ) The Bar Council of India may, at any time, call for the record of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act which has been disposed of by a State Bar Council or a committee thereof, and`
  line `from which no appe al lies, for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the legality or propriety of such disposal`
  line `and may pass such orders in relation thereto as it may think fit.`
  line `( 2 ) No order which prejudicially affects any person shall be passed under this section without giving him`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `4 [ 48AA. Review. ― The Bar Council of India or any of its committee s, other than its disciplinary`
  line `committee, may of its own motion or otherwise review any order, within sixty days of the date of that order,`
  line `passed by it under this Act.]`
  line `48B. Power to give directions. ― ( 1 ) Fo r the proper and efficient discharge of the functions of a State Bar`
  line `Council or any committee thereof, the Bar Council of India may, in the exercise of its powers of general`
  line `supervision and control, give such directions to the State Bar Council or any comm ittee thereof as may appear`
  line `to it to be necessary, and the State Bar Council or the committee sha ll comply with such directions.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 35 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 19 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 37 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-26
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Page 26`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  sourcePage 26
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `( 2 ) Where a State Bar Council is unable to perform its functions for any reason whatsoever, the Bar`
  line `Council of India may, witho ut prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, give such directions to`
  line `the ex officio member thereof as may appear to it to be necessary, and such directions shall have effect,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the rules made b y the State Bar Council.]`
  line `49. General power of the Bar Council of India to make rules. ― 1 [( 1 )] The Bar Council of India may`
  line `make rules for discharging its functions under this Act, and, in particular, such rules may prescribe —`
  line `2 [( a ) the conditions subject to which an advocate may be entitled to vote at an election to the State Bar`
  line `Council i ncluding the qualifications or disqualifications of voters, and the manner in which an electoral`
  line `roll of voters may be prepared and revised by a State Bar Council;`
  line `( ab ) qualifications for membership of a Bar Council and the disqualifications for such memb ership;`
  line `( ac ) the time within which and the manner in which effect may be given to the proviso to sub - section`
  line `( 2 ) of section 3;`
  line `( ad ) the manner in which the name of any advocate may be prevented from being entered in more`
  line `than one State roll;`
  line `( ae ) the ma nner in which the seniority among advocates may be determined;`
  line `3 [( af ) the minimum qualifications required for admission to a course of degree in law in any`
  line `recognised University;]`
  line `( ag ) the class or category of persons entitled to be enrolled as advocates;`
  line `( ah ) the conditions subject to which an advocate shall have the right to practise and the circumstances`
  line `under which a person shall be deemed to practise as an advocate in a court;]`
  line `( b ) the form in which an application shall be made for the transfer of the name of an advocate from`
  line `one State roll to another;`
  line `( c ) the standards of professional conduct and etiquette to be observed by advocates;`
  line `( d ) the standards of legal education to be observed by Universities in India and the inspection of`
  line `Universities f or that purpose;`
  line `( e ) the foreign qualifications in law obtained by persons other than citizens of India which shall be`
  line `recognised for the purpose of admission as an advocate under this Act;`
  line `( f ) the procedure to be followed by the disciplinary committee of a State Bar Council and by its own`
  line `disciplinary committee;`
  line `( g ) the restrictions in the matter of practice to which senior advocates shall be subject;`
  line `4 [( gg ) the form of dresses or robes to be worn by advocates, having regard to the climatic conditions,`
  line `appearing before any court or tribunal;]`
  line `( h ) the fees which may be levied in respect of any matter under this Act;`
  line `5 [( i ) general principles for guidance of State Bar Councils and the manner in which directions issued`
  line `or orders made by the Bar Council o f India may be enforced;`
  line `1. Section 49 re - numbered as sub - section ( 1 ) of that section by Act 60 of 1973, s. 38 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 20, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 38, for clause ( af ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 20, for clause ( i ) (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-27
  sectionNo (27)
