  title `Page 27`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  sourcePage 27
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `( j ) any other matter which may be prescribed:]`
  line `4 [Provided that no rules made with reference to clause ( c ) or clause ( gg ) shall have effect unless they have`
  line `been approved by the Chief Justice of India:]`
  line `1 [Provided further that] n o rules made with reference to clause ( e ) shall have effect unless they have been`
  line `approved by the Central Government.`
  line `2 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the first proviso to sub - section ( 1 ), any rules made with`
  line `reference to clause ( c ) or clause ( gg ) of the said sub - section and in force immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Advocates (Amendment) Act, 1973 (60 of 1973), shall continue in force until altered or`
  line `repealed or amended in accordance with the provisions of this Act.]`
  line `3 [ 49A. Power of C entral Government to make rules. ― ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act including rules with`
  line `respect to any matter for which the Bar Council of India or a State Bar Council has power to make rules.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for —`
  line `( a ) qualifications for membership of a Bar Council and disqualifications for such membership;`
  line `( b ) the manner in which the Bar Council of India may exercise supervision and control over State Bar`
  line `Councils and the manner in which the directions issued or orders made by the Bar Council of India may`
  line `be enforced;`
  line `( c ) the class or category of persons entitled to be enrolled as advocates under this Act;`
  line `( d ) the category of persons who may be exempted from undergoing a course of training and passing`
  line `an examination prescribed under clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 24;`
  line `( e ) the manner in which seniority among advocates may be determined;`
  line `( f ) the proc edure to be followed by a disciplinary committee of a Bar Council in hearing cases and the`
  line `procedure to be followed by a disciplinary committee of the Bar Council of India in hearing appeals;`
  line `( g ) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Rules under this section may be made either for the whole of India or for all or any of the Bar`
  line Councils.
  line `( 4 ) If any provision of a rule made by a Bar Council is repugnant to any provision of a rule made by the`
  line `Central Government under this section, then, the rule un der this section, whether made before or after the rule`
  line `made by the Bar Council, shall prevail and the rule made by the Bar Council shall, to the extent of the`
  line `repugnancy, be void.`
  line `4 [( 5 ) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following`
  line `the ses sion or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 38, for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 21 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 39, for sub - section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
