obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `50. Repeal of certain enactments. ― ( 1 ) On the date on which a State Bar Council is constituted under`
  line `this Act, the provisions of sections 3 to 7 (inclusive), sub - sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) of section 9, section 15 and`
  line `section 20 of the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926), shall stand repealed in the territory for which`
  line `the State Bar Council is constituted.`
  line `( 2 ) On the date on which Chapter III comes into force, the following shall stand repealed, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) sections 6, 7, 18 and 37 of the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), and so much of sections`
  line `8, 9, 16, 17, 19 and 41 of that Act as relate to the admission and enrolment of legal practitioners;`
  line `( b ) sections 3, 4 and 6 of the Bombay Pleaders A ct, 1920 (Bombay Act 17 of 1920);`
  line `( c ) so much of section 8 of the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926), as relates to the admission`
  line `and enrolment of legal practitioners;`
  line `( d ) the provisions of the Letters Patent of any High Court and of any other la w in so far as they relate`
  line `to the admission and enrolment of legal practitioners.`
  line `( 3 ) On the date on which Chapter IV comes into force, the following shall stand repealed, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) sections 4, 5, 10 and 20 of the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), and so much of sections`
  line `8, 9, 19 and 41 of that Act as confer on legal practitioners the right to practise in any court or before any`
  line `authority or person;`
  line `( b ) sections 5, 7, 8 and 9 of the Bombay Pleaders Act, 1920 (Bombay Act 17 of 1920);`
  line `( c ) section 14 of the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926) and, so much of sections 8 and 15 of`
  line `that Act as confer on legal practitioners the right to practise in any court or before any authority or person;`
  line `( d ) the Supreme Court Advocates (Practice in High Courts) Act, 1951 (18 of 1951);`
  line `( e ) the provisions of the Letters Patent of any High Court and of any other law conferring on legal`
  line `practitioners the right to practise in any cour t or before any authority or person.`
  line `( 4 ) On the date on which Chapter V comes into force, the following shall stand repealed, namely: ―`
  line `( a ) sections 12 to 15 (inclusive), sections 21 to 24 (inclusive) and sections 39 and 40 of the Legal`
  line `Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), and so 82 much of sections 16, 17 and 41 of that Act as relate to the`
  line `suspension, removal or dismissal of legal practitioners;`
  line `( b ) sections 24 to 27 (inclusive) of the Bombay Pleaders Act, 1920 (Bombay Act 17 of 1920);`
  line `( c ) sections 10 to 13 (inclusive) of the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926);`
  line `( d ) the provisions of the Letters Patent of any High Court and of any other law in so far as they relate`
  line `to the suspension, removal or dismissal of legal practitioners.`
  line `( 5 ) When the who le of this Act has come into force —`
  line `( a ) the remaining provisions of the Acts referred to in this section which do not stand repealed by`
  line `virtue of any of the foregoing provisions of this section (except sections 1, 3 and 36 of the Legal`
  line `Practitioners Act, 1 879) (18 of 1879) shall stand repealed;`
  line `( b ) the enactment specified in the Schedule shall stand repealed to the extent mentioned therein.`
  line `1 [ ( 6 ) On the date on which section 45A of the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) comes into force,`
  line `sections 1, 3 and 36 of the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879) shall stand repealed. ]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30 - 9 - 2024).`
