obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line 29
  line `51. Rule of construction. ― On and from the appointed day, references in any enactment to an advocate`
  line `enrolled by a High Court in any form of words shall be construed as references to an advocate enrolled under`
  line `this Act.`
  line `52. Saving. ― Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to affect the power of the Supreme Court to make rules`
  line `under article 145 of the Constitution ―`
  line `( a ) for laying down the conditions subject to which a senior advocate shall be entitled to practise in`
  line `that Court;`
  line `( b ) for determining the per sons who shall be entitled to 1 [act or plead] in that Court.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `T EMPORARY AND TRANSITIONAL PROVISIONS`
  line `53. Elections to first State Bar Council. ― Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the elected`
  line `members of a State Bar Council, constituted for the first time under this Act, shall be elected by and from`
  line `amongst advocates, vakils, pleaders and attorneys who, on the date of the election, are entitled as of right to`
  line `practise in the High Court and are ordinarily practising within the territory for which the Bar Council is to be`
  line constituted.
  line `Explanation. ― Where the territory for which the Bar Council is to be constituted includes a Union`
  line `territory, the expression “ High Court ” shall include the court of the Judicial Commissioner of that Union`
  line territory.
  line `54. Term of office of members of first State Bar Coun cils. ― Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, the term of office of the 2 *** elected members of 3 *** a State Bar Council constituted for the first`
  line `time, shall be two years from the date of the first meeting of the Council:`
  line `4 [Provided that such mem bers shall continue to hold office until the State Bar Council is reconstituted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.]`
  line `55. Rights of certain existing legal practitioners not affected. ― Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act. —`
  line `( a ) every plea der or vakil practising as such immediately before the date on which Chapter IV comes`
  line `into force (hereinafter in this section referred to as the said date) by virtue of the provisions of the Legal`
  line `Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), the Bombay Pleaders A ct, 1920 (Bombay Act 17 of 1920), or any`
  line `other law who does not elect to be, or is not qualified to be, enrolled as an advocate under this Act;`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [( c ) every mukhtar practising as such immediately before the said date by virtue of th e provisions of`
  line `the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), or any other law, who does not elect to be, or is not`
  line `qualified to be, enrolled as an advocate under this Act;`
  line `( d ) every revenue agent practising as such immediately before the said date by v irtue of the provisions`
  line `of the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), or any other law;]`
  line `shall, notwithstanding the repeal by this Act of the relevant provisions of the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879`
  line `(18 of 1879), the Bombay Pleaders Act, 1920 (Bomba y Act 17 of 1920), or other law, continue to enjoy the`
  line `same rights as respects practice in any court or revenue office or before any authority or person and be subject`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 70 of 1993, s. 9, for “act” (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1993).`
  line `2. The words “ nominated and ” omitted by Act 14 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30 - 3 - 1962).`
  line `3. The words “ the Bar Council of India and ” omitted by Act 21 of 1964, s. 22 ( w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964 ).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. ( w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964 ).`
  line `5. Clause ( b ) omitted by Act 107 of 1976, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1977).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 23, for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
