obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `to the disciplinary jurisdiction of the same authority which he enjoyed or, as the case may be, to which he was`
  line `subject immediately before the said date and accordingly the relevant provisions of the Acts or law aforesaid`
  line `shall have effect in relation to such persons as if they had not been repealed.`
  line `56. Dissolution of existing Bar Councils. ― ( 1 ) On the constitution under this Act of a State Bar Council,`
  line `other than the Bar Council of Delhi (hereinafter referred to as the new Bar Council) —`
  line `( a ) all properties and assets vesting in the corresponding Bar Council shall vest in the new Bar`
  line Council;
  line `( b ) all rights, liabilities, and obligations of the corresponding Bar Council, whether arising out of any`
  line `contract or otherwise, shall be the rights, liabilities and obligations respectively of the new Bar Council;`
  line `( c ) all proceedings pending before the corresponding Bar Council in respect of any disciplinary matter`
  line `or otherwise shall stand transferred to the new Bar Council.`
  line `( 2 ) In this section, “ corresponding Bar Council ” in relation to a State Bar Council, other than the Bar`
  line `Council of Delhi, means th e Bar council for the High Court in the territory for which the State Bar Council is`
  line `constituted under this Act.`
  line `57. Power to make rules pending the constitution of a Bar Council. ― Until a Bar Council is`
  line `constituted under this Act, the power of that Bar Cou ncil to make rules under this Act shall be exercised —`
  line `( a ) in the case of the Bar Council of India, by the Supreme Court;`
  line `( b ) in the case of a State Bar Council, by the High Court.`
  line `1 [ 58. Special provisions during the transitional period. ― ( 1 ) Where a State Bar Council has not been`
  line `constituted under this Act or where a State Bar Council so constituted is unable to perform its functions by`
  line `reason of any order of a court or otherwise, the functions of that Bar Council or of any committee thereof, in`
  line `so far as t hey relate to the admission and enrolment of advocates, shall be performed by the High Court in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Until Chapter IV comes into force, a State Bar Council or a High Court performing the functions of a`
  line `State Bar Council may enrol any person to be an advocate on a State roll, if he is qualified to be so enrolled`
  line `under this Act, notwithstanding that no rules have been made under section 28 or that the rules so made have`
  line `not been approved by the Bar Council of India, and every person so enrolled shall, until that Chapter comes`
  line `into force, be entitled to all the rights of practice conferred on an advocate under section 14 of the Indian Bar`
  line `Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926).`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, every person who, immediately before the 1st day of`
  line `December, 1961, was an advocate on the roll of any High Court under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926`
  line `(38 of 1926) or who has been enrolled as an advocate under this Act shall, until Chapter IV com es into force,`
  line `be entitled as of right to practise in the Supreme Court, subject to the rules made by the Supreme Court in this`
  line behalf.
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding the repeal by sub - section ( 2 ) of section 50 of the provisions of the Legal Practitioners`
  line `Act, 1879 (18 of 1879) or of the Bombay Pleaders Act, 1920 (Bombay Act 17 of 1920) 2 [or of any other law`
  line `relating to the admission and enrolment of legal practitioners, the provisions of the Acts and law aforesaid]`
  line `and any rules made thereunde r in so far as they rel ate to 3 [the renewal or the issue by way of renewal] of a`
  line `certificate to a legal practitioner authorising him to practise shall have effect until Chapter IV comes into force`
  line `and, accordingly, every certificate issued or renewed to a legal practitioner (who is not enrolled as an advocate`
  line `under this Act) which is or purports to be issued or renewed under the provisions of either of the aforesaid`
  line `1. I ns. by Act 14 of 1962, s. 4 ( w.e.f. 30 - 3 - 1962 ).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1962, s. 3, for certain words (retrospectively).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 24, for “ the issue and renewal ” (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
