obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line 31
  line `Acts 1 [or of the other law] during the period beginning with the 1st day of December, 1961 and ending with`
  line `the date on which Chapter IV comes into force, shall be deemed to have been validly issued or renewed.`
  line `2 [ 58A. Special provisions with respect to certain advocates. ― ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act, all advocates who, immediately before the 26th day of July, 1948, were entitled to practise in the`
  line `High Court in Allahabad or the Chief Court in Oudh and who under the provisions of the United Provinces`
  line `High Courts (Amalgamation) Order, 1948 were recognised as advocates entitled to practise in the new High`
  line `Court of Judicature at Allahabad but whose names were not formally entered on the roll of advocates of that`
  line `High Court merely by reason of the non - paym ent of the fee payable to the Bar Council of the said High Court,`
  line `and all advocates who were enrolled as such between the said date and the 26th day of May, 1952, shall, for`
  line `the purposes of clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 17 be deemed to be person s who were entered as`
  line `advocates on the roll of the said High Court under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926) and every`
  line `such person may, on an application being made in this behalf, be admitted as an advocate on the State roll of`
  line `Uttar Pradesh.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, all advocates who, immediately before the 10th day of`
  line `October, 1952, were entitled to practise in the High Court of Hyderabad but whose names were not formally`
  line `entered on the roll of advocates of that Hig h Court merely by reason of the non - payment of the fee payable to`
  line `the Bar Council of the said High Court shall, for the purposes of clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 17, be`
  line `deemed to be persons who were entered as advocates on the roll of the said H igh Court under the Indian Bar`
  line `Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926 ) and every such person may, on an application being made in this behalf, be`
  line `admitted as an advocate on the State roll of Andhra Pradesh or of Maharashtra.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything containe d in this Act, all advocates who, immediately before the 1st day of`
  line `May, 1960, were entitled to practise in the High Court of Bombay and who applied to get their names entered`
  line `on the roll of advocates of the High Court of Gujarat under the provisions of se ction 8 of the Indian Bar`
  line `Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926) but whose names were not so entered by reason of the repeal of the said`
  line `provision shall, for the purposes of clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 17, be deemed to be persons who`
  line `were entered as advocates on the roll of the High Court of Gujarat under the said Act and every such person`
  line `may, on an application being made in this behalf, be admitted as an advocate on the State roll of Gujarat.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, all persons who, immediately before the 1st day of`
  line `December, 1961, were advocates on the roll of the court of Judicial Commissioner in any Union territory`
  line `under any law in force in that territory shall, for the purposes of clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of sect ion 17, be`
  line `deemed to be persons who were entered as advocates on the roll of a High Court under the Indian Bar`
  line `Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926) and every such person may, on an application made in this behalf, be`
  line `admitted as an advocate on the State roll ma intained in respect of that Union territory.`
  line `3 [ 58AA. Special provisions in relation to the Union territory of Pondicherry. ― ( 1 ) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, all persons who, immediately before the date on which the provisions of`
  line `Chapter III are brought into force in the Union territory of Pondicherry, were entitled to practise the`
  line `profession of law (whether by way of pleading or acting or both) under any law in force in the said Union`
  line `territory or who would have been so entitled had they not been in public service on the said date, shall for the`
  line `purposes of clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 17, be deem ed to be persons who were entered as`
  line `advocates on the roll of a High Court under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926), and every such`
  line `person may, on an application made in this behalf within such time as may be specified by the Bar Council of`
  line `Mad ras, be admitted as an advocate on the State roll maintained in respect of the said Union territory.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, every person who, immediately before the date on`
  line `which the provisions of Chapter IV are brought into f orce in the Union territory of Pondicherry, was`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 1962, s. 3 ( w.e.f. 30 - 3 - 1962 ).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1964, s. 25 (w.e.f. 16 - 5 - 1964).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and Sch. (w.e.f. 24 - 5 - 1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
