  title `Page 32`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  sourcePage 32
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line 32
  line `practising the profession of law (whether by way of pleading or acting or both or in any other way) by virtue`
  line `of the provisions of any law in force in the said Union territory, who does not elect to be or is not qualified to`
  line `be, enrolled as an advocate under sub - section ( 1 ), shall, notwithstanding the repeal of the relevant provisions`
  line `of such law by the Pondicherry (Extension of Laws) Act, 1968 (26 of 1968), continue to enjoy the same rights`
  line `as respects practi ce in any court or revenue office or before any authority or person and be subject to the`
  line `disciplinary jurisdiction of the same authority which he enjoyed, or, as the case may be, to which he was`
  line `subject, immediately before the said date and accordingly th e relevant provisions of the law aforesaid shall`
  line `have effect in relation to such persons as if they had not been repealed.]`
  line `1 [ 58AB. Special provisions with respect to certain persons enrolled by Mysore State Bar Council. -`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any judgment, decree or order of any court or any`
  line `resolution passed or direction given by the Bar Council of India, every person who was admitted as an`
  line `advocate on the State roll by the State Bar Council of Mysore during the period beginnin g with the 28th day`
  line `of February, 1963, and ending on the 31st day of March, 1964, on the basis of his having obtained a certificate`
  line `of pleadership from the High Court of Mysore, shall, save as otherwise provided, be deemed to have been`
  line `validly admitted as an advocate on that State roll and accordingly entitled to practise the profession of law`
  line `(whether by way of pleading or acting or both):`
  line `Provided that where any such person has elected to be enrolled as an advocate on the roll of any other`
  line `State Bar Coun cil, his name shall be deemed to have been struck off the roll of the State Bar Council of`
  line `Mysore from the date he was enrolled by the other State Bar Council:`
  line `Provided further that the seniority of such person, whether his name is borne on the State roll of the State`
  line `Bar Council of Mysore, or on the State roll of any other Bar Council, shall, for the purposes of clause ( d ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ) of section 17, be determined by reckoning the 16th day of May, 1964, as the date of`
  line admission.]
  line `2 [ 58AC. Special pro visions with respect to certain persons enrolled by Uttar Pradesh State Bar`
  line `Council. ― Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any judgment, decree or order of any court,`
  line `every person who was enrolled as an advocate by the High Court during the per iod beginning with the`
  line `2nd day of January, 1962 and ending on the 25th day of May, 1962 and was subsequently admitted as an`
  line `advocate on the State roll by the State Bar Council of Uttar Pradesh shall be deemed to have been validly`
  line `admitted as an advocate o n that State roll from the date of his enrolment by the High Court and accordingly`
  line `entitled to practise the profession of law (whether by way of pleading or acting or both).`
  line `58AD. Special provisions with respect to certain persons migrating to India. ― Notwithstanding the`
  line `repeal by this Act of the provisions of the Legal Practitioners Act, 1879 (18 of 1879), or of any other law`
  line `relating to the admission and enrolment of legal practitioners (hereafter in this section referred to as such Act`
  line `or law), ever y person who migrates to the territory of India from any area which, before the 15th day of`
  line `August, 1947, was comprised within India as defined in the Government of India Act, 1935, and who has,`
  line `before such migration, been a pleader, mukhtar or revenue age nt in any such area under any law in force`
  line `therein, may be admitted and enrolled under the relevant provisions of such Act or law as a pleader, mukhtar`
  line `or, as the case may be, revenue agent, if he ―`
  line `( a ) makes an application for the purpose to the appropriate authority under such Act or law; and`
  line `( b ) is a citizen of India and fulfils other conditions, if any, specified in this behalf by the appropriate`
  line `authority aforesaid,`
  line `and notwithstanding the r epeal by this Act of the relevant provisions of such Act or law, every pleader,`
  line `mukhtar or revenue agent so enrolled shall have the same rights as respects practice in any court or revenue`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 5 - 6 - 1968).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 60 of 1973, s. 40 (w.e.f. 31 - 1 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
