obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line 33
  line `office or before any other authority or person and be subject to th e disciplinary jurisdiction of the same`
  line `authority to which he would be subject under the relevant provisions of such Act or law as if they had not`
  line `been repealed and accordingly, those provisions shall have effect in relation to such persons.`
  line `58AE. Special provisions in relation to the Union territory of Goa, Daman and Diu. ― ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, all persons who, immediately before the date on which the`
  line `provisions of Chapter III are brought into force in the Union territory of Go a, Daman and Diu, were entitled to`
  line `practise the profession of law (whether by way of pleading or acting or both) under any law in force in the`
  line `said Union territory or who would have been so entitled had they not been in public service on the said date,`
  line `sha ll, for the purpose of clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 17, be deemed to be persons who were entered`
  line `as advocates on the roll of a High Court under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926), and every such`
  line `person may, on an application made in this behalf within such time as may be specified by the Bar Council of`
  line `Maharashtra, be admitted as an advocate on the State roll maintained in respect of the said Union territory:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub - section shall not apply to any pe rson who, on the date of the`
  line `application aforesaid, was not a citizen of India.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, every person who, immediately before the date on`
  line `which the provisions of Chapter IV are brought into force in the Union ter ritory of Goa, Daman and Diu, was`
  line `practising the profession of law (whether by way of pleading or acting or both or in any other way) by virtue`
  line `of the provisions of any law in force in the said Union territory, or who does not elect to be or is not qualifi ed`
  line `to be enrolled as an advocate under sub - section ( 1 ), shall, notwithstanding the repeal by this Act of the`
  line `relevant provisions of such law, continue to enjoy the same rights as respects practice in any court or revenue`
  line `office or before any other authorit y or person and be subject to the disciplinary jurisdiction of the same`
  line `authority which he enjoyed, or, as the case may be, to which he was subject, immediately before the said date`
  line `and accordingly the relevant provisions of the law aforesaid shall have ef fect in relation to such persons as if`
  line `they had not been repealed.`
  line `( 3 ) On the date on which this Act or any part thereof comes into force in the Union territory of Goa,`
  line `Daman and Diu, the law in force in that Union territory which corresponds to this Act or such part and which`
  line `does not stand repealed by virtue of the provisions of section 50 of this Act, shall also stand repealed.`
  line `[ 58AF. Special provisions in relation to Jammu and Kashmir ]. ― Omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `Reorganisation (Adaptation of Cen tral Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18 - 3 -`
  line `2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020,`
  line `notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23 - 10 - 2020).]`
  line `1 [ 58AG. Special provisions in rela tion to articled clerks. ― Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, every person who, immediately before the 31st day of December, 1976, has commenced his articleship`
  line `and passed the Preliminary examination, for the purpose of enrolment as an attorney of the High Court at`
  line `Cal cutta in accordance with the rules made under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 34, before the omission of that`
  line `sub - section by the Advocates (Amendment) Act, 1976 (107 of 1976), be admitted as an advocate on the State`
  line `roll if he ―`
  line `( i ) passes, on or before the 31st day of December, 1980, ―`
  line `( a ) the Final examination in a case where such person has, before the 31st day of December,`
  line `1976, passed the Intermediate examination,`
  line `( b ) the Intermediate and the Final examinations in any other case.`
  line `Explanation. ― For the purpos e of this clause, the High Court at Calcutta may prescribe such rules as`
  line `may be necessary under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 34, specifying the nature of the examinations and any`
  line `other matter relating thereto;`
  line `1. Ins. by Ac t 38 of 1977, s. 7 (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-34
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Page 34`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  sourcePage 34
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line 34
  line `( ii ) makes an application for such enrolment in accordance with the provisions of this Act; and`
  line `( iii ) fulfils the conditions specified in clauses ( a ), ( b ), ( e ) and ( f ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 24.]`
  line `58B. Special provision relating to certain disciplinary proceedings. ― ( 1 ) As from the 1st day of`
  line `September, 1963, every proceeding in respect of any disciplinary matter in relation to an existing advocate of`
  line `a High Court shall, save as provided in the first proviso to sub - section ( 2 ), be disposed of by the State Bar`
  line `Council in relation to that High Court, as if the existing advocate had been enrolled as an advocate on its roll.`
  line `( 2 ) If immediately before the said date, there is any proceeding in respect of any disciplinary matter in`
  line `relation to an existing advocate pending b efore any High Court under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926`
  line `(38 of 1926), such proceeding shall stand transferred to the State Bar Council in relation to that High Court, as`
  line `if it were a proceeding pending before the corresponding Bar Council under claus e ( c ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 56:`
  line `Provided that where in respect of any such proceeding the High Court has received the finding of a`
  line `Tribunal constituted under section 11 of the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926), the High Court shall`
  line `dispose of the case and it shall be lawful for the High Court to exercise for the purpose all powers conferred`
  line `on it under section 12 of the said Act as if that section had not been repealed:`
  line `Provided further that where the High Court has referred back any case for further inquiry under sub -`
  line `section ( 4 ) of section 12 of the said Act, the proceeding shall stand transferred to the State Bar Council in`
  line `relation to the High Court as if it were a proceeding pending before the corresponding Bar Council under`
  line `clause ( c ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 56.`
  line `( 3 ) If immediately before the said date there is any proceeding in respect of any disciplinary matter`
  line `pending in relation to any pleader, vakil, mukhtar or attorney, who has been enrolled as an advocate on any`
  line `State roll under the Act, such proceeding shall stand transferred to the State Bar Council on the roll of which`
  line `he has been enrolled and be dealt with under this Act as if it were a proceeding arising against him thereunder.`
  line `( 4 ) In this section “ existing advocate ” means a person who was enrolled as an advocate on the roll of any`
  line `High Court under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926) and who, at the time when any proceeding`
  line `in respect of any disciplinary matter is initiated against him, is not enrolled as an advocate on a State roll`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of this section shall have effect, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act.]`
  line `59. Removal of difficulties. ― ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `part icularly in relation to the transition from the enactments repealed by this Act to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as a ppear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line difficulty.
  line `( 2 ) An order under sub - section ( 1 ) may be made so as to have retrospective effect from a date not earlier`
  line `than the 1st day of December, 1961. ]`
  line `1 [ 60. Power of Central Government to make rules. ― ( 1 ) Until rules in respect of any matter under this`
  line `Act are made by a State Bar Council and approved by the Bar Council of India, the power to make rules in`
  line `respect of that matter shall be exercisable by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Gove rnment after consultation with the Bar Council of India may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make rules under sub - section ( 1 ) either for any State Bar Council or generally for all`
  line `State Bar Councils and the rules so made shall have effect, notwit hstanding anything contained in this Act.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1962, s. 4 (w.e.f. 14 - 9 - 1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-35
  sectionNo (35)
