  title `Page 35`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  sourcePage 35
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line 35
  line `( 3 ) Where in respect of any matter any rules are made by the Central Government under this section for`
  line `any State Bar Council, and in respect of the same matter, rules are made by the State Bar Council and`
  line `approved by the Bar Council of India, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the rules made by it in respect of such matter shall cease to be in force in relation to that Bar`
  line `Council with effect from such date as may be sp ecified in the notification and on the issue of such`
  line `notification, the rules made by the Central Government shall, accordingly, cease to be in force except as`
  line `respects things done or omitted to be done before the said date.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
